descript.abstract: Current extent of indigenous vegetation types and subtypes of the City of Cape Town: 20130822
descript.purpose: Floristically based vegetation units of Cape Town
descript.supplinf:
Based on SANBI's 2004 national vegetation map at the 1:50 000 scale prepared by Barry Low and modified by Tony Rebelo and Barrie Low, incorporating the SANParks vegetation map (primarily the subtypes in Peninsula Sandstone Fynbos and Peninsula Granite Fynbos, with a few more water bodies and strandveld types added on the southern Peninsula (Milkwoods and Forest. etc.) with additional refinement by the Environmental Resource Management Department of the City of Cape Town.
Being submitted by SANBI to the National Vegetation Map committee for acceptance into the National Vegetation Map.
'Southern Afromontane Forest' subtypes have no current known ecological significance, but are retained for future work, as such patterns are expected.
